[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "ref": "80:1",
    "arabic": "عَبَسَ وَتَوَلَّىٰٓ",
    "transliteration": "AAabasa watawalla",
    "translation": "He frowned and turned away",
    "notes": "A study of the Verses that follow reveal the identity of ‘He’ here to be the Prophet (peace on him) himself. The use of the third person pronoun instead of the direct ‘You’ is obviously a subtle divine way to mitigate the embarrassment of a direct accusation. But, nevertheless, the accusation is there in the public domain! It shows that Allah Almighty had kept a close watch on even the minutest thing that the Prophet did, to steer him away from any wrong move on his part. It also shows up the transparency in which the Prophet truthfully conveyed the divine Message, even when it contained something disparaging to his own person."
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "ref": "80:2",
    "arabic": "أَن جَآءَهُ ٱلۡأَعۡمَىٰ",
    "transliteration": "An jaahu alaAAma",
    "translation": "That the blind man came to him.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 3,
    "ref": "80:3",
    "arabic": "وَمَا يُدۡرِيكَ لَعَلَّهُۥ يَزَّكَّىٰٓ",
    "transliteration": "Wama yudreeka laAAallahu yazzakka",
    "translation": "And what do you know? He might reform [to become a righteous man].",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 4,
    "ref": "80:4",
    "arabic": "أَوۡ يَذَّكَّرُ فَتَنفَعَهُ ٱلذِّكۡرَىٰٓ",
    "transliteration": "Aw yaththakkaru fatanfaAAahu alththikra",
    "translation": "Or, he might deliberate, and the deliberation might benefit him.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 5,
    "ref": "80:5",
    "arabic": "أَمَّا مَنِ ٱسۡتَغۡنَىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Amma mani istaghna",
    "translation": "Now he who is well-to-do,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 6,
    "ref": "80:6",
    "arabic": "فَأَنتَ لَهُۥ تَصَدَّىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Faanta lahu tasadda",
    "translation": "To him you pay attention!",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 7,
    "ref": "80:7",
    "arabic": "وَمَا عَلَيۡكَ أَلَّا يَزَّكَّىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Wama AAalayka alla yazzakka",
    "translation": "And [even when] it is not your responsibility if he would not reform!",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 8,
    "ref": "80:8",
    "arabic": "وَأَمَّا مَن جَآءَكَ يَسۡعَىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Waamma man jaaka yasAAa",
    "translation": "And he who comes to you in earnest,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 9,
    "ref": "80:9",
    "arabic": "وَهُوَ يَخۡشَىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Wahuwa yakhsha",
    "translation": "And fears (Allah),",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 10,
    "ref": "80:10",
    "arabic": "فَأَنتَ عَنۡهُ تَلَهَّىٰ",
    "transliteration": "Faanta AAanhu talahha",
    "translation": "By him then are you distracted!",
    "notes": "From the narration in these ten Verses, we can surmise that the Prophet was trying to convince some rich man of the Makkan community of the necessity of Monotheism as against polytheism the man had been following. In the meantime, a blind man came and sought the Prophet’s attention on some religious matter. The Prophet felt distracted, and hence this divine admonition to him."
  },
  {
    "id": 11,
    "ref": "80:11",
    "arabic": "كَلَّآ إِنَّهَا تَذۡكِرَةٞ",
    "transliteration": "Kalla innaha tathkiratun",
    "translation": "No! [Your resentment at the blind man’s intrusion is not right.] This [Qur’aan] is only an open source of divine Admonition to recite.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 12,
    "ref": "80:12",
    "arabic": "فَمَن شَآءَ ذَكَرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Faman shaa thakarahu",
    "translation": "So whoso wills may recite it and take heed from",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 13,
    "ref": "80:13",
    "arabic": "فِي صُحُفٖ مُّكَرَّمَةٖ",
    "transliteration": "Fee suhufin mukarramatin",
    "translation": "In records honourable,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 14,
    "ref": "80:14",
    "arabic": "مَّرۡفُوعَةٖ مُّطَهَّرَةِۭ",
    "transliteration": "MarfooAAatin mutahharatin",
    "translation": "Exalted and purified,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 15,
    "ref": "80:15",
    "arabic": "بِأَيۡدِي سَفَرَةٖ",
    "transliteration": "Biaydee safaratin",
    "translation": "By hands of scribes,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 16,
    "ref": "80:16",
    "arabic": "كِرَامِۭ بَرَرَةٖ",
    "transliteration": "Kiramin bararatin",
    "translation": "Noble and virtuous!",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 17,
    "ref": "80:17",
    "arabic": "قُتِلَ ٱلۡإِنسَٰنُ مَآ أَكۡفَرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Qutila alinsanu ma akfarahu",
    "translation": "Man be damned, how ungrateful is he!",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 18,
    "ref": "80:18",
    "arabic": "مِنۡ أَيِّ شَيۡءٍ خَلَقَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Min ayyi shayin khalaqahu",
    "translation": "Out of what thing did He create him?",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 19,
    "ref": "80:19",
    "arabic": "مِن نُّطۡفَةٍ خَلَقَهُۥ فَقَدَّرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Min nutfatin khalaqahu faqaddarahu",
    "translation": "HE created him out of fertilized ovum and then moulded him in due proportion.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 20,
    "ref": "80:20",
    "arabic": "ثُمَّ ٱلسَّبِيلَ يَسَّرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Thumma alssabeela yassarahu",
    "translation": "And then made the path of life convenient for him.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 21,
    "ref": "80:21",
    "arabic": "ثُمَّ أَمَاتَهُۥ فَأَقۡبَرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Thumma amatahu faaqbarahu",
    "translation": "And then He caused him to die and consigned him to dust.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 22,
    "ref": "80:22",
    "arabic": "ثُمَّ إِذَا شَآءَ أَنشَرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Thumma itha shaa ansharahu",
    "translation": "And then, whenever He wishes, He will raise him back to life.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 23,
    "ref": "80:23",
    "arabic": "كَلَّا لَمَّا يَقۡضِ مَآ أَمَرَهُۥ",
    "transliteration": "Kalla lamma yaqdi ma amarahu",
    "translation": "No! Man did certainly not carry out what Allah had asked him to do.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 24,
    "ref": "80:24",
    "arabic": "فَلۡيَنظُرِ ٱلۡإِنسَٰنُ إِلَىٰ طَعَامِهِۦٓ",
    "transliteration": "Falyanthuri alinsanu ila taAAamihi",
    "translation": "Let man just look at his food.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 25,
    "ref": "80:25",
    "arabic": "أَنَّا صَبَبۡنَا ٱلۡمَآءَ صَبّٗا",
    "transliteration": "Anna sababna almaa sabban",
    "translation": "[To enable man to get his food] We poured water [rain] in showers,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 26,
    "ref": "80:26",
    "arabic": "ثُمَّ شَقَقۡنَا ٱلۡأَرۡضَ شَقّٗا",
    "transliteration": "Thumma shaqaqna alarda shaqqan",
    "translation": "And We pierced the soil, so that it got soaked [with rain water].",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 27,
    "ref": "80:27",
    "arabic": "فَأَنۢبَتۡنَا فِيهَا حَبّٗا",
    "transliteration": "Faanbatna feeha habban",
    "translation": "Then We caused grain to grow therein,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 28,
    "ref": "80:28",
    "arabic": "وَعِنَبٗا وَقَضۡبٗا",
    "transliteration": "WaAAinaban waqadban",
    "translation": "And grapevines and vegetables,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 29,
    "ref": "80:29",
    "arabic": "وَزَيۡتُونٗا وَنَخۡلٗا",
    "transliteration": "Wazaytoonan wanakhlan",
    "translation": "And olive-trees and palm-trees,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 30,
    "ref": "80:30",
    "arabic": "وَحَدَآئِقَ غُلۡبٗا",
    "transliteration": "Wahadaiqa ghulban",
    "translation": "And luxuriant orchards,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 31,
    "ref": "80:31",
    "arabic": "وَفَٰكِهَةٗ وَأَبّٗا",
    "transliteration": "Wafakihatan waabban",
    "translation": "And fruits and fodder",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 32,
    "ref": "80:32",
    "arabic": "مَّتَٰعٗا لَّكُمۡ وَلِأَنۡعَٰمِكُمۡ",
    "transliteration": "MataAAan lakum walianAAamikum",
    "translation": "As provision for you and your cattle.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 33,
    "ref": "80:33",
    "arabic": "فَإِذَا جَآءَتِ ٱلصَّآخَّةُ",
    "transliteration": "Faitha jaati alssakhkhatu",
    "translation": "Then as the deafening blast occurs",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 34,
    "ref": "80:34",
    "arabic": "يَوۡمَ يَفِرُّ ٱلۡمَرۡءُ مِنۡ أَخِيهِ",
    "transliteration": "Yawma yafirru almaro min akheehi",
    "translation": "On the Day when every man would flee from his brother,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 35,
    "ref": "80:35",
    "arabic": "وَأُمِّهِۦ وَأَبِيهِ",
    "transliteration": "Waommihi waabeehi",
    "translation": "And his mother and his father;",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 36,
    "ref": "80:36",
    "arabic": "وَصَٰحِبَتِهِۦ وَبَنِيهِ",
    "transliteration": "Wasahibatihi wabaneehi",
    "translation": "And his spouse and his children.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 37,
    "ref": "80:37",
    "arabic": "لِكُلِّ ٱمۡرِيٕٖ مِّنۡهُمۡ يَوۡمَئِذٖ شَأۡنٞ يُغۡنِيهِ",
    "transliteration": "Likulli imriin minhum yawmaithin shanun yughneehi",
    "translation": "On that Day everyone among them will be preoccupied with his own individual concerns.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 38,
    "ref": "80:38",
    "arabic": "وُجُوهٞ يَوۡمَئِذٖ مُّسۡفِرَةٞ",
    "transliteration": "Wujoohun yawmaithin musfiratun",
    "translation": "Faces that Day would be beaming,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 39,
    "ref": "80:39",
    "arabic": "ضَاحِكَةٞ مُّسۡتَبۡشِرَةٞ",
    "transliteration": "Dahikatun mustabshiratun",
    "translation": "Cheerful and joyous.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 40,
    "ref": "80:40",
    "arabic": "وَوُجُوهٞ يَوۡمَئِذٍ عَلَيۡهَا غَبَرَةٞ",
    "transliteration": "Wawujoohun yawmaithin AAalayha ghabaratun",
    "translation": "And faces that Day would be gloomy,",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 41,
    "ref": "80:41",
    "arabic": "تَرۡهَقُهَا قَتَرَةٌ",
    "transliteration": "Tarhaquha qataratun",
    "translation": "Darkness covering them.",
    "notes": ""
  },
  {
    "id": 42,
    "ref": "80:42",
    "arabic": "أُوْلَـٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلۡكَفَرَةُ ٱلۡفَجَرَةُ",
    "transliteration": "Olaika humu alkafaratu alfajaratu",
    "translation": "Those would be the ones suppressing the Truth, the ones wicked!",
    "notes": ""
  }
]